people_also_ask.question: Does New Hampshire have storms?
people_also_ask.answer_source: Weather Hazards | New Hampshire Department of Health and Human ...
people_also_ask.answer_html: Extreme weather events common to New Hampshire include severe coastal storms, winter storms, cold waves, thunderstorms, floods, and tropical cyclones. Winter storms and snow are an important feature of New Hampshire's climate.

value.text: Extreme weather events common to New Hampshire include severe coastal storms, winter storms, cold waves, thunderstorms, floods, and tropical cyclones. Winter storms and snow are an important feature of New Hampshire's climate.

people_also_ask.question: Do hurricanes happen in New Hampshire?
people_also_ask.answer_source: What kinds of disasters does New Hampshire experience? - NH.gov

people_also_ask.answer_html: Floods, hurricanes and severe winter storms are the most common natural disasters in New Hampshire, although earthquakes and high wind events are also possible.

people_also_ask.question: What are the weather hazards in New Hampshire?
people_also_ask.answer_source: Natural Disasters in New Hampshire: What Is the Risk? - Primal Survivor
people_also_ask.answer_html: New Hampshire has approximately 19,000 miles of rivers and streams. Snowmelt, heavy rains, and ice jams can cause these rivers to swell, resulting in widespread floods. Heavy rains can also cause deadly flash floods in the state. As a result, many areas of New Hampshire are at high risk when it comes to flooding.Mar 16, 2023

people_also_ask.question: What is the climate in NH?
people_also_ask.answer_html: New Hampshire experiences a humid continental climate (Köppen climate classification Dfa in some southern areas, Dfb in most of the state, and Dfc subarctic in some northern highland areas), with warm, humid summers, and long, cold, and snowy winters. Precipitation is fairly evenly distributed all year.
